      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/69",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ وَلَدِ اَلزِّنَا أَ يُبَاعُ وَ يُشْتَرَى وَ يُسْتَخْدَمُ قَالَ \"نَعَمْ \" قُلْتُ فَيُسْتَنْكَحُ قَالَ \"نَعَمْ وَ لاَ تَطْلُبُ وَلَدَهَا \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3840 - It is narrated from Abdullah bin Sinan who said: I asked Abu Abdillah (as) about a child born out of wedlock, can he be sold, purchased, and employed as a servant?\nImam (as) said: \"Yes.\"\nI said: \"Can he be married?\"\nImam (as) said: \"Yes, but do not seek her offspring.\""
        ]
      }
    },
